---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const steps = [
  {
    title: 'Setting Up Your Development Environment',
    content: `
      Before you start developing Discord bots, you'll need to set up your development environment:
      
      1. Install Node.js (version 16.9.0 or higher)
      2. Set up a code editor (we recommend Visual Studio Code)
      3. Create a Discord account and access the Developer Portal
      4. Create a new application in the Discord Developer Portal
    `,
    link: '/docs/discord-js/getting-started'
  },
  {
    title: 'Creating Your First Bot',
    content: `
      Let's create a basic Discord bot:

      1. Create a new Discord application
      2. Add a bot user to your application
      3. Get your bot token
      4. Set up a new Node.js project
      5. Install discord.js
      6. Write your first bot code
    `,
    link: '/tutorials/first-bot'
  },
  {
    title: 'Next Steps',
    content: `
      After creating your first bot, explore these topics:

      1. Implementing slash commands
      2. Handling events
      3. Database integration
      4. Deployment and hosting

      Choose your learning path based on your needs and interests.
    `,
    link: '/content'
  }
];
---

<Layout title="Getting Started - Discord Bot Development">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-8">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Getting Started with Discord Bot Development</h1>
    
    <div class="space-y-12">
      {steps.map((step, index) => (
        <div class="bg-[#2B2D31] p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">
            <span class="text-[#5865F2] mr-2">{index + 1}.</span>
            {step.title}
          </h2>
          <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none mb-4">
            {step.content}
          </div>
          <a 
            href={step.link}
            class="inline-block bg-[#5865F2] hover:bg-[#4752C4] px-6 py-3 rounded-md font-medium transition-colors"
          >
            Continue â†’
          </a>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 bg-[#2B2D31] p-6 rounded-lg">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Ready to Explore More?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-6">
        Once you've completed the getting started guide, you can:
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <a 
          href="/bot-development"
          class="bg-[#1E1F22] hover:bg-[#2B2D31] p-4 rounded-lg text-center transition-colors"
        >
          Bot Development
        </a>
        <a 
          href="/api-integration"
          class="bg-[#1E1F22] hover:bg-[#2B2D31] p-4 rounded-lg text-center transition-colors"
        >
          API Integration
        </a>
        <a 
          href="/best-practices"
          class="bg-[#1E1F22] hover:bg-[#2B2D31] p-4 rounded-lg text-center transition-colors"
        >
          Best Practices
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
